title: Boys Soccer Roundup for Tuesday, Oct. 20
text:
Boys Soccer Roundup for Tuesday, Oct. 20 6:56 p.m. EDT October 20, 2015 Boys soccer 3 CONNECT TWEET LINKEDIN COMMENT EMAIL MORE 
GMC Tournament Play-In Round 
Woodbridge 7, Timothy Christian 4: Andrew Fuentes scored four goals and Steven Luzuriaga recorded the hat trick to help Woodbridge (3-13-2) to the next round. Matthew Parris had two goals for Timothy Christian (12-5). 
Middlesex 4, Edison Academy 0: Mathias Squilliace netted two goals for Middlesex (12-6). Elvis Perez and Paolo Marina followed his act with scores of their own. 
J.F. Kennedy 5, South Amboy 1: Noah Miranda led the way by striking twice and adding an assisst. Victor Milton, Dimeji Oyinkolade and Nikhil Thapa each scored for J.F. Kennedy (4-12). 
Perth Amboy 5, Perth Amboy Tech 0: Five different players scored for Perth Amboy (8-8-2) to help them walk away with the victory. Axel Moyano, Joseph Torres, Daniel Calderon, Piero Morales and Francisco Medina each entered the scoring column. 
Regular Season 
Plainfield 6, Rahway: Emerson Abarca and Boima Fenfoaquee both beat the goal keeper twice. Chris Navarette and William Guzman completed the scoring affair with goals of their for Plainfield (9-3-1). Jonathan Hernandez dished out two assists in the win. Read or Share this story: http://mycj.co/1LJiQUI TOP VIDEOS
